description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for December 10, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs.  Our astrologer has analyzed the movements of the planets and the alignment of the stars to bring you the most accurate and up-to-date horoscope predictions for the day ahead. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope: Read your today's astrological predictions

description: An advocate commissioner in Sambhal requested a 15-day extension to submit a survey report on the Shahi Jama Masjid, citing health reasons.  This delay, following previous extensions and clashes during a survey, has drawn objections from the mosque committee's counsel, who questions the commissioner's motives. The court will await further directions due to a Supreme Court stay order.
title: Sambhal mosque surveyor cites health issues, seeks 15-day extension

description: West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee downplayed threats from Bangladeshi figures to occupy Indian states, attributing them to illness.  She urged calm and responsible behavior amidst communal unrest in Bangladesh, blaming a political party for stoking tensions. Banerjee cautioned against spreading rumors and fake videos, emphasizing Bengal's commitment to secularism and cooperation with the central government on external affairs.
title: Let Centre take call on B'desh, our view will align with it: Mamata

description: Justice Shekhar Kumar Yadav, an Allahabad High Court judge who recently endorsed the Uniform Civil Code (UCC) at a VHP event, previously advocated for cow protection as a fundamental Hindu right. The VHP's legal cell is promoting UCC, Waqf Board amendments, and freeing temples from government control.
title: Judge backing UCC at VHP event wanted cow as 'national animal'

description: The Common University Entrance Test (CUET) will revert to a solely computer-based format in 2025 with standardized 60-minute papers.  All questions will be mandatory.  These changes follow logistical and technical issues that plagued previous CUET administrations, including exam cancellations, answer key errors, and a paper leak.  The UGC aims to improve efficiency and credibility with these revisions.
title: CUET '25 overhaul: Computer-based tests to make comeback

description: A 42-year-old Rajasthani cook, Sukhdev Prajapati, died of a heart attack after being allegedly assaulted in Gujarat. He had mistakenly prepared 'kaju katli' instead of 'laddoos' for a wedding, angering the host and his relatives who then confronted him.
title: Sweet mix-up turns bitter: Cook dies after dessert dispute

description: Telangana CM A Revanth Reddy unveiled the official Telangana Thalli statue, warning against any alterations or insults to it.  The statue's unveiling coincided with the 2009 announcement of the separate statehood process.  An official annual celebration, Telangana Thalli Avatarana Utsavam, will now take place on December 9th.
title: CM unveils T'gana 'mother' statue, says bid to alter will invite action

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah hinted at restoring the 4% Muslim quota scrapped by the BJP, citing the latter's affidavit in court.  This sparked a debate in the assembly, with BJP demanding proof.  Simultaneously, the government restricted a Panchamasali Lingayat protest for reservation, leading to further clashes.
title: Siddaramaiah may restore 4% Muslim quota in Karnataka

description: Israel launched over 100 airstrikes targeting Syrian military sites, including a suspected chemical weapons research center, weapons depots, and air defense installations. The strikes follow Assad's removal and increased volatility in the Golan Heights, where Israel has deployed troops.
title: Israel hits over 100 Syrian sites linked to Assad regime

description: A three-day relic-discovery drive in Lakkundi, India, unearthed an 8ft, 12th-century inscribed stone tablet.  Locals handed over historical artifacts, and five historic temples-turned-houses were identified. Authorities plan to create a museum and are working towards adding Lakkundi to UNESCO's World Heritage Site list.
title: Historical dig: Karnataka village unearths centuries-old secrets
BJP steps up attack on Congress for 'Soros links' of Gandhis

description: BRS legislators in Telangana were detained by police for wearing T-shirts protesting a perceived connection between a Congress leader and the Adani group. BRS leader KTR accused Congress of hypocrisy, citing different stances on Adani at the national and state levels, and questioned Rahul Gandhi's position.
title: BRS MLAs sporting Revanth-Adani tees held by Telangana cops

description: The Indian government is considering referring the 'one nation, one election' bill to a parliamentary panel for wider consultations. This aims to achieve consensus on the proposal, which seeks to synchronize elections nationwide. While the government emphasizes the reform's potential to save resources, the opposition criticizes it as undemocratic and unconstitutional, citing logistical challenges and threats to federalism.
title: Government may refer 'one nation, one election' bill to JPC

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced the Bima Sakhi scheme on Monday, aiming to boost women's representation in LIC's agent force. Currently, women comprise 28% of LIC agents, up from six lakh in 2017 to nearly 7.5 lakh in 2023. The program will initially recruit 25,000 women, with a target of two lakh over three years.
title: 2 lakh women will be inducted as LIC agents in 3 years: FM Sitharaman
'Reform, Perform, Transform' powered India's growth: PM Modi

description: The INDIA bloc is preparing to submit a resolution to remove Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar, citing his conduct during parliamentary proceedings. Opposition parties claim they have enough signatures to initiate the removal process, marking a historic first in India's parliamentary history.
title: Opposition parties join hands in bid to oust Rajya Sabha chairman

description: A BEST bus in Kurla, Mumbai, crashed into multiple vehicles and pedestrians, resulting in four fatalities and 29 injuries. The driver, arrested for potential brake failure, lost control, creating a scene of chaos.  Authorities are investigating the cause, with locals blaming inadequate infrastructure for the tragedy.
title: 4 dead, 29 hurt as BEST bus rams vehicles, pedestrians in Mumbai

description: Revenue secretary Sanjay Malhotra has been appointed as the new RBI governor, succeeding Shaktikanta Das.  The 56-year-old IIT Kanpur and Princeton University alumnus will begin his three-year term on December 11th.  Malhotra's appointment marks a continuation of bureaucratic leadership at the central bank, following Das's tenure of close coordination with the government.
title: Revenue secretary Sanjay Malhotra to be next RBI governor

description: The Undertaker revealed he would never transition to a commentary role in WWE, finding the job undesirable.  He prefers observing from Gorilla position or the production truck. Though retired from in-ring competition, The Undertaker mentors younger wrestlers like Damian Priest, offering direct advice and praising rising stars such as Bron Breakker, Jey Uso, and LA Knight.
title: The Undertaker’s no-go zone: A WWE task he’d never do

description: Sources told the New York Post that 26-year-old Luigi Mangione had a personal interest in hating the medical community -- his grandmother died in 2013 and grandfather in 2017. A manifesto was found on him apart from the gun, a silencer and four fake IDs with names that he used in New York City. The manifesto rallied against the US healthcare industry.
title: Brian Thompson killer suspect identified as ex-Ivy League student Luigi Mangione

description: Parliamentary proceedings were disrupted as BJP and Congress clashed over allegations of Congress's links with George Soros and BJP's shielding of the Adani group.  Both Lok Sabha and Rajya Sabha witnessed repeated adjournments amidst heated exchanges and protests by opposition members demanding discussions on both issues.
title: House adjourned after ruckus over Soros-Congress, Adani issues

description: Telangana High Court revoked ex-BRS MLA Chennamaneni Ramesh's Indian citizenship, deeming him a German citizen. He was fined ₹30 lakh for concealing this and misleading the court. Ramesh's German naturalization in the 1990s and retention of his German passport despite regaining Indian citizenship in 2008 led to this unprecedented decision.
title: 4-time MLA stripped of Indian citizenship, fined

description: India is closely monitoring the evolving situation in Syria, emphasizing the importance of preserving the nation's unity and territorial integrity.  The government advocates for a peaceful, inclusive Syrian-led political process, while ensuring the safety of Indian nationals in Damascus.  India remains concerned about regional stability given Syria's proximity to key Gulf partners.
title: India calls for peaceful & inclusive Syrian-led political process

description: India's Foreign Secretary Vikram Misri visited Dhaka to discuss concerns regarding the safety of minorities in Bangladesh.  While reaffirming India's commitment to the interim government, Misri addressed attacks on minorities and cultural properties. Bangladesh acknowledged the concerns but labeled them an internal matter, also raising concerns about former PM Sheikh Hasina's presence in India.
title: Foreign secretary meets Yunus, flags attacks on minorities
Brothers in arms: Soldiers fulfil dead comrade’s duty at daughter’s wedding

description: Josh Allen made history with three passing and three rushing touchdowns in a single game, but the Bills lost to the Rams.  Defensive struggles and special teams mistakes, including a blocked punt returned for a touchdown, overshadowed Allen's 400+ yard performance.  A late-game timeout call by Coach McDermott drew criticism from Tom Brady and fans alike.
title: Sean McDermott points at defense post Rams defeat

description: Elon Musk visited Capitol Hill with his son, X-Æ-12, regarding the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE).  A video of Musk's son advising him to "Save America" and "Help Trump" went viral.  The child's comments sparked reactions online, with some predicting future leadership roles. Musk will lead DOGE, partnering with Vivek Ramaswamy, aiming to improve government efficiency and accountability.
title: Elon Musk's son X-Æ-12 has these two KRAs for him: Save America & ...

description: Odisha prepares to host the 18th Pravasi Bharatiya Diwas from January 8-10, 2025, marking the state's first time hosting the event.  Chief Minister Majhi emphasized showcasing Odisha's culture and achieving international cleanliness standards.  The event will feature dignitaries like the Prime Minister and President, alongside cultural festivals and tours to prominent tourist destinations for the expected 7,500 delegates.
title: Odisha gears up for historic Pravasi Bharatiya Diwas 2025 in Bhubaneswar

description: Pakistan's internet speeds plummeted in October, ranking among the slowest globally, according to Ookla's Speedtest Global Index.  Users experienced frequent slowdowns and connectivity issues, alongside restricted VPN access.  The government's installation of a Chinese-built national internet firewall is blamed for the disruptions.
title: Online surveillance slows mobile, internet speed in Pakistan

description: India's rural literacy rate has significantly increased to 77.5% in 2023-24, driven by a surge in female literacy.  Government programs like ULLAS, focusing on foundational skills and vocational training, have contributed to this growth, with over 2 crore learners enrolled.  However, challenges remain in achieving 100% literacy due to diverse languages and cultural contexts.
title: Female literacy surge in rural India: Govt's key initiatives and challenges

description: Nearly 8 lakh students in India have enrolled in AI courses at the secondary level, while over 50,000 have opted for it at the senior secondary level for the 2024-25 academic year. The government emphasized the growing importance of AI education, aligning with the National Education Policy 2020's focus on 21st-century skills.
title: Over 8 lakh CBSE students enrolled in AI courses for 2024-25 session

description: China's market regulator is investigating Nvidia for potential anti-monopoly violations, possibly in retaliation for recent US semiconductor restrictions.  The investigation centers around Nvidia's 2020 acquisition of Mellanox Technologies and alleged breaches of agreed-upon conditions.
title: China launches investigation into US' biggest and most-valuable chip company

description: The UK government is considering lifting the ban on Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS), an Islamist militant group that recently overthrew the Assad regime in Syria. This potential shift hinges on HTS upholding its promises to protect minority rights and ensure citizen safety. While HTS has historical ties to al-Qaeda, it claims to have severed those connections.
title: UK indicates lifting ban on HTS if it delivers on its promises
Three dead, several injured after bus hits pedestrians, vehicles in Mumbai

description: Foreign secretary Vikram Misri met with Bangladeshi officials in Dhaka to address strained bilateral relations following recent attacks on minorities in Bangladesh.  Both sides acknowledged the need to resolve outstanding issues and expressed optimism for a stronger, mutually beneficial partnership going forward. Misri emphasised India's expectation of a constructive approach from Bangladesh in addressing these concerns.
title: 'Help clear the clouds': Indian foreign secy meets B'desh interim chief Yunus amid rising tensions

description: Keshav Maharaj's stunning five-wicket haul in the fourth innings propelled South Africa to a 2-0 series whitewash against Sri Lanka. His performance, his fourth five-wicket haul in the final innings of a Test, puts him among South African bowling greats.
title: Average 17.76, strike rate 35.5! Maharaj stands tall behind Steyn

description: A Volaris flight from León to Tijuana was diverted to Guadalajara after a passenger attempted to hijack the plane.  The 31-year-old man, claiming his family was threatened, assaulted a flight attendant and tried to enter the cockpit.  He was apprehended by the crew and handed over to authorities upon landing. The flight later continued to its original destination.
title: Man tries to hijack Mexican plane and divert it to US, arrested

description: Over 180 people were massacred in Cité Soleil, Haiti, over the weekend, according to the UN. A gang leader allegedly ordered the killings as revenge for his son's death, which he believed was caused by witchcraft.  Elderly Vodou practitioners were specifically targeted, with many bodies burned or disposed of at sea. The violence highlights Haiti's escalating gang crisis and dire security situation.
title: 'Bad spell': How 'witchcraft' sparked nearly 200 executions in Haiti

description: BJP leaders condemned PDP leader Iltija Mufti's statement criticizing Hindutva as a "disease," calling it irresponsible and divisive.  Mufti clarified her stance, differentiating between Hindutva, which she labeled an ideology of hate, and Hinduism, which she viewed as a religion promoting love and compassion, similar to Islam.
title: 'Irresponsible': BJP hits out at Iltija Mufti for 'Hindutva' statement

description: Former Indian pacer Dodda Ganesh has issued a stern warning against Rohit Sharma opening the batting in the third Test at the Gabba. Ganesh believes Rohit's current form and the challenging Australian conditions make it a risky move.
title: 'Foolhardy': Former pacer blasts suggestions for Rohit to open

description: Jeff Bezos and Elon Musk are like rival Jedi Masters battling for control of the galaxy's destiny. Bezos, the Obi-Wan Kenobi of space, envisions protecting Earth, the "Chosen One," by moving industries to orbital sanctuaries—akin to peaceful Alderaan. Musk, the bold Luke Skywalker, dreams of leading humanity to Mars, a Tatooine-like refuge, to survive inevitable cataclysms. Their rivalry mirrors a Star Wars saga, from dueling over NASA’s “Death Star” contracts to trading jabs like lightsaber strikes. Whether Bezos’ industrial "Rebel Alliance" or Musk’s Martian "Empire" prevails, their cosmic clash will shape humanity’s next chapter in this galactic epic.
title: Star Wars: How Musk vs Bezos space race could reshape humanity

description: ​The first arrest in connection with the murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson was made on Monday in Pennsylvania. The man was nabbed while trying to use a fake ID at a McDonald's and was taken into custody by cops in Altoona, about 233 miles west of New York City.
title: Person of interest held in UnitedHealthcare CEO shooting case

description: In Jharkhand's Palamu district, an eight-year-old boy was tragically strangled by his aunt, Sunita Devi.  Driven by superstitious beliefs and revenge, Devi suspected the boy's grandmother of witchcraft, blaming her for the death of Devi's five-month-old son.  The incident occurred on Sunday in Saltua village, and the boy's body was recovered from an agricultural field.
title: Woman strangles nephew to avenge son's death 'due to black magic'

description: Former Indian cricketer Mohammed Kaif criticizes India's bowling strategy against Travis Head, highlighting their failure to exploit his weakness outside the off-stump, similar to how Australia targets Virat Kohli. Kaif emphasizes the need for a planned attack from the first ball, asserting that the Australian team isn't unbeatable.
title: 'Virat Kohli ki kamzori log pakad ke rakhe hue hai' : Mohammad Kaif

description: Ahead of the third Test against Australia in Brisbane, Indian cricketer Rishabh Pant shared a heartwarming moment with a young girl in Adelaide.  The playful interaction, captured on video, went viral, showcasing Pant's approachable nature.  This lighthearted moment followed India's crushing defeat in the second Test, a match that saw Australia level the series 1-1.
title: Watch: Pant’s sweet moment with a little girl in Adelaide
Constitution debate: 'PM Modi to address Lok Sabha on Dec 14'

description: Syrian jihadist rebels declared victory on Sunday, announcing the capture of Damascus and the end of President Bashar al-Assad's 13-year rule.  Assad's ouster marks a major turning point, ending a 50-year dynasty.  Celebrations erupted as opposition flags, symbolizing resistance to Assad's regime, replaced his portraits across the nation and in diaspora communities.
title: Symbolic shift: Syrian embassies start flying new rebel flag

description: An Indian Army soldier, Havildar V Subbaiah Varikunta, was tragically killed in a mine blast while on patrol along the Line of Control (LoC) in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch district. He was part of a routine patrol in the Thanedar Tekri area when he accidentally stepped on a mine.
title: Army jawan killed in mine blast in J&K's Poonch

description: The Supreme Court granted permanent commission to a woman Army officer, rectifying her wrongful exclusion from consideration.  The court emphasized fairness, ensuring equal treatment for all officers regardless of litigation status.  The officer, wrongly denied permanent commission despite a favorable 2014 ruling, will receive retroactive benefits including seniority and arrears.
title: 'What is sauce for goose ought to be sauce for gander': SC grants relief to woman officer

description: The Mahila Samman Savings Certificate (MSSC) scheme, launched in March 2023, offers a 7.5% interest rate to women and minor girls until March 31, 2025. Over 43 lakh accounts were opened by October 2024. Deposits range from ₹1,000 to ₹2 lakh for a two-year term.
title: Mahila samman savings certificate: Last few months to apply for scheme

description: The UPSC has announced the Civil Services Examination (CSE) Mains 2024 results on December 9, 2024. Candidates can check their results and the list of shortlisted candidates on upsc.gov.in. Successful candidates will advance to the personality round. The CSE, conducted in three phases, held its Prelims on June 16 and Mains from September 20-29.
title: UPSC CSE Mains Result 2024: Names of shortlisted candidates released
Man threatens to 'kill' Andhra Pradesh deputy CM Pawan Kalyan

description: Rajya Sabha proceedings were disrupted by opposition protests targeting PM Modi and Gautam Adani.  Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar warned of a "deep state" threat and called for unity, referencing a meeting with Modi and Rahul Gandhi. Despite appeals, protests persisted, leading to another meeting scheduled for December 10.
title: 'Must neutralise deep state': VP Dhankar amid Rajya Sabha ruckus

description: Syrian rebels ousted President Bashar al-Assad, ending his family's rule.  The rebel coalition, Hayat Tahrir al-Sham, captured Aleppo and Damascus. Assad's military was weakened by corruption. Hezbollah fighters were absent due to conflict in Lebanon. Russia's support waned due to its focus on Ukraine.  This event reshapes Middle Eastern power dynamics and raises concerns about Iran's nuclear ambitions.
title: US-designated terrorist is leader of Syria: will Iran go nuclear now?

description: Bollywood buzzed with exciting news! Deepika Padukone made a rare appearance with daughter Dua. Abhishek Bachchan addressed rumors, hinting at future family plans.  Rajkummar Rao confirmed "Stree 3" is in development. Amitabh Bachchan and Allu Arjun exchanged praise. Ranbir Kapoor discussed "Animal" becoming a trilogy and updates on "Brahmastra 2."
title: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: A Tamil film, Amaran, mistakenly displayed a student's phone number, leading to a flood of unwanted calls.  Producers apologized and removed the number after a legal notice demanding compensation for the distress caused.
title: Amaran gets this 'change' after Rs 1.1 crore lawsuit from engineering student

description: India commissioned INS Tushil, a stealth frigate built in Russia, strengthening defense ties and future collaborations in AI, cybersecurity, and space exploration.  The frigate, equipped with Brahmos missiles and advanced weaponry, is part of a four-ship deal, with two more being built in India.
title: Missile frigate INS Tushil inducted into Indian Navy in Russia

description: During a Test match, Indian captain Rohit Sharma's on-field frustration was caught on the stump mic.  He angrily questioned a teammate's positioning, shouting "Why are you running behind?" The teammate explained his location, leading to a heated exchange.  Commentator Harbhajan Singh humorously recalled his own famous on-field quip.  India ultimately suffered a heavy defeat in the match.
title: 'Kya peeche peeche bhagta hai tu': Rohit loses cool

description: Indian grandmaster D Gukesh lost the 12th game of the World Chess Championship against Ding Liren, leveling the score at 6-6. Gukesh's earlier win had given him a brief lead, but Liren's victory with white pieces brought the match to a tie. With two games remaining, the championship is likely headed for tiebreakers.
title: Gukesh succumbs to Liren in 12th game of World Chess Championship

description: The Aam Aadmi Party and Bharatiya Janata Party are engaged in a creative poster war for the upcoming Delhi assembly polls, using the film "Pushpa 2" as their theme.  AAP's poster features Arvind Kejriwal, while BJP's poster showcases Virendra Sachdeva.  Both parties are actively campaigning on social media, with AAP aiming for a fourth term and BJP seeking to regain control after over two decades.
title: 'Jhukega Nahi' vs 'Rappa-Rappa': AAP, BJP in Pushpa 2-inspired poster war

description: The UPSC has announced the Civil Services Examination (CSE) Mains 2024 results on December 9. Candidates can check their results at upsc.gov.in. Those qualified will proceed to the personality round. The CSE is conducted in three phases: Prelims (June 16), Mains (September 20-29), and the interview round. Check the direct link here.
title: UPSC CSE Mains Result 2024 declared, check direct link here

description: The Indian government is preparing to introduce a bill for simultaneous elections nationwide, aiming to streamline the electoral process.  The proposal requires constitutional amendments and faces opposition criticism regarding practicality and democratic implications.  A committee recommends national dialogue before implementation, potentially after 2029.
title: Centre may table 'one nation, one election' Bill soon: Reports

description: YesMadam, a Noida-based salon home service startup, is under fire for allegedly terminating around 100 employees who reported work-related stress in an internal survey.
title: Startup fires 100 employees after ‘fooling’ them with mental health survey

description: Despite Rohit Sharma's poor performance and questionable captaincy decisions in the Adelaide Test loss to Australia, former cricketer and national selector Jatin Paranjape backs the Indian captain to regain his form.  Paranjape expects Rohit to return to opening the batting in the next Test and believes his class will ultimately prevail.
title: 'Let's not forget that he is a...': Ex-selector backs Rohit

description: Sanjay Malhotra, the Revenue Secretary, has been appointed as new Reserve Bank of India (RBI) governor by the Narendra Modi government. Malhotra will succeed Shakikanta Das whose tenure is scheduled to end on December 10, 2024.
title: Who is Sanjay Malhotra? Revenue secy appointed new RBI governor

description: Mohammed Siraj and Travis Head have been fined and received demerit points for their on-field confrontation during the second Border-Gavaskar Test. Siraj was penalized for using inappropriate language and gestures after dismissing Head, while Head was sanctioned for his response. Both players accepted the sanctions imposed by the match referee after a brief exchange following Head's dismissal.
title: Siraj, Travis penalised for fiery outburst during Adelaide Test

description: Opposition parties are initiating proceedings to remove vice president Jagdeep Dhankhar from his position as Rajya Sabha chairman.  This follows escalating tensions with the ruling BJP, particularly after allegations linking Congress leaders to financier George Soros and disputes over parliamentary procedures.  Both Houses of Parliament were adjourned amidst the uproar.
title: Oppn to move no-confidence motion against VP Dhankhar: Report

description: Sanjay Malhotra, a 1990-batch IAS officer, has been appointed as the 26th RBI Governor, succeeding Shaktikanta Das.  Malhotra's three-year term begins Wednesday.  His background includes roles in finance, taxation, and IT, both within the state and central government.  Das's term will be concluded on Tuesday after stabilising markets following his predecessor's exit.
title: Revenue secretary Sanjay Malhotra appointed new RBI governor

description: During the Chiefs-Chargers game, Taylor Swift's absence from Arrowhead Stadium was noted by broadcasters, coinciding with the final show of her record-breaking 'Eras Tour' in Vancouver.  Cris Collinsworth, a self-proclaimed Swiftie, congratulated Swift on her successful tour, highlighting its impact and her influence extending into the sports world through her relationship with Travis Kelce.
title: Look at this cute message by Mike Tirico and Cris Collinsworth for Taylor Swift

description: A fire erupted at the Jungle Jamboree Restaurant in Delhi's Rajouri Garden market, prompting a swift response from 10 fire tenders.  Over 20 people were present when the fire broke out, leading to dramatic escapes and one injury during the rescue.  The cause of the fire remains under investigation, and authorities have secured the area.
title: Watch: People jump off roof to escape fire in Delhi's Rajouri Garden

description: India and Bangladesh held high-level talks in Dhaka, addressing concerns over minority safety and attacks on properties.  Foreign Secretary Misri reiterated India's commitment to the interim government and discussed strengthening bilateral ties across trade, connectivity, and cultural cooperation.
title: At foreign secy meet, India flags attacks on minorities, religious sites in Bangladesh

description: YesMadam, a salon home service startup, is facing backlash after a leaked email suggested they fired employees who reported feeling stressed in a company survey.  The incident sparked online outrage and raised questions about the company's handling of workplace stress.  While the email's authenticity remains unconfirmed, it has ignited a discussion on workplace well-being and survey ethics.
title: Popular Indian company fires 'stressed' employees after survey!

description: South Africa beat Sri Lanka in the second Test. They won by 109 runs.  South Africa swept the series 2-0.  They now lead the World Test Championship. Keshav Maharaj took five wickets in the final innings. South Africa's win keeps their hopes of reaching the WTC final alive. They will play Pakistan next at home.
title: South Africa leave behind Australia, India to spice up race to WTC final

description: Former Indian captain Krishnamachari Srikkanth criticised Mohammed Siraj's send-off to Travis Head during the second Test in Adelaide which was played under lights.  Srikkanth believed Siraj's reaction was unwarranted, especially after Head's dominant 140-run innings. He emphasised performance over aggression, suggesting Siraj should have acknowledged Head's brilliant run-a-ball knock instead of confronting him.
title: What rubbish is this? Siraj slammed by ex-India captain

description: 20-year-old Thai folk singer Chayada Prao-hom died on December 8th from complications arising from neck massages at a parlour in Udon Thani.  She experienced escalating paralysis after multiple sessions involving neck-twisting techniques.  An investigation revealed that several masseuses at the parlour were unlicensed, raising concerns about improper practices. Authorities are investigating the parlour's compliance with regulations.
title: 20-year-old Thai folk singer Chayada Prao-hom passes away

description: Kapil Dev expressed concern over Vinod Kambli's struggles, urging him to prioritize his well-being. Kambli's recent appearance at a memorial event highlighted his difficulties, prompting support from the cricketing fraternity, including the 1983 World Cup-winning team and Sunil Gavaskar, who pledged to help him recover.
title: 'We can't look after ... ': Kapil's plea to Kambli

description: Nobel Peace Prize laureate Narges Mohammadi, currently imprisoned in Iran, connected with the Nobel Committee via video call from prison. Granted temporary release for medical treatment, she joyfully recounted hearing the news of her award amidst chants of 'Azadi' (freedom) from fellow inmates.
title: Watch: Out of jail on medical leave, Iran’s Nobel laureate sings 'Bella Ciao'

description: Indian captain Rohit Sharma explained the team's decision to ban fans from net sessions in Australia.  He emphasized the private nature of practice discussions and the need to avoid public interference.  The team's net sessions became a talking point after reports of insensitive comments from spectators.
title: Rohit reveals why Team India banned fans from nets in Australia

description: Rebels liberated Saydnaya prison near Damascus, freeing thousands of prisoners. Families rushed to the notorious facility, searching for missing loved ones.  The prison, infamous for its brutality under the Assad regime, held an estimated 20,000 prisoners, with thousands more missing across Syria.  The liberation marks a significant moment in the regime's collapse.
title: As Syria’s 'slaughterhouse' prisons empty, families search for missing inmates

description: An Indian-American family, subjected to racist harassment on a United Airlines bus, plans to press charges against the identified perpetrator, Arlene Consuela. The family received support and the perpetrator's identity from her own family and friends after the video of the incident went viral.
title: Racist rant: Indian-American family to press charges against woman

description: Air India, back with Tata Group, is expanding its fleet significantly.  The airline has ordered an additional 100 Airbus aircraft, including 10 A350s and 90 A320 Family aircraft. This adds to their previous order of 470 aircraft, bringing the total to 570.  This expansion aims to meet growing passenger demand and establish Air India as a world-class airline.
title: Air India to buy 100 more Airbus after record 470-aircraft order in 2023

description: West Bengal chief minister Mamata Banerjee urged calm amidst provocative remarks from Bangladeshi politicians claiming rights over Indian territories.  She emphasized unity and condemned attacks on minorities in Bangladesh, cautioning against escalating tensions and advocating responsible discussion of the situation.
title: 'Will we have lollipop?': Mamata hits out at Bangladeshi politicians

description: People gathered and sat around lighting fire as cold wave gripped the Kashmir valley and mercury dipped to sub-zero temperatures in Srinagar on Monday.
title: Cold wave grips Kashmir as temperatures dip; people light 'Kangris' to keep warm

description: A SpiceJet flight en route from Delhi to Shillong was diverted to Patna on Monday morning due to a technical issue.  The aircraft landed safely at Patna's Jay Prakash Narayan International Airport. The airline is making alternative travel arrangements for the affected passengers.
title: Delhi-Shillong flight lands in Patna after technical glitch
2 trainee pilots dead, 2 injured in car accident near Pune

description: Elon Musk criticized US funding of opposing sides in the Syrian conflict, highlighting a 2016 report of CIA-backed and Pentagon-backed militias clashing.  Syrian rebels claimed control of Homs, celebrating Assad's reported departure to Russia after 24 years in power.
title: 'Our tax dollars are somehow funding both sides': Musk on Syrian crisis

description: The Supreme Court has demanded a detailed report from the Manipur government concerning properties affected by the recent unrest.  The report must include information on burnt and looted properties, identifying current occupants and original owners.  The Court also seeks details on legal actions taken against trespassers, emphasizing accountability for the widespread destruction and displacement.
title: SC seeks sealed report from Manipur govt on action taken

description: HDFC Bank has raised its Marginal Cost of Funds-Based Lending Rate (MCLR) by up to 5 basis points for short-term loans.  The overnight MCLR now stands at 9.20%, effective December 7, 2024.
title: HDFC Bank hikes MCLR by up to 5 basis points; here are the latest lending rates

description: Noida International Airport conducted its first successful flight test on Monday, a crucial step towards its April 2025 opening. An IndiGo aircraft performed takeoff and landing maneuvers as part of the validation process. Data collected will be submitted to the DGCA for licensing approval.
title: Watch: Noida International Airport conducts first flight validation test

description: A Chennai-Kochi flight with 90 people on board made an emergency landing back in Chennai due to a mechanical failure shortly after takeoff. The pilot's quick thinking ensured the safe return of all passengers and crew.  The aircraft is currently undergoing repairs, and passengers are awaiting the rescheduled departure. An investigation into the mechanical issue is underway.
title: How pilot's swift action averted major disaster on Chennai-Kochi flight

description: Syrian rebels, led by Hayat Tahrir al-Sham, seized control of Bashar al-Assad's palace after he fled to Russia, ending his 13-year rule.  The rebels discovered Assad's extravagant car collection, sparking online outrage. The collection included luxury brands like Ferrari, Aston Martin, and Rolls-Royce, highlighting the stark contrast between Assad's lavish lifestyle and the suffering of Syrian citizens.
title: Watch: Syrian rebels find Ferraris, Rolls-Royces in Bashar al-Assad's palace

description: Adam Gilchrist believes India's supporting bowlers need to step up their game to match Jasprit Bumrah's level. He praised Bumrah's performance but pointed out Siraj and Rana's struggles in Adelaide. Gilchrist also advocated for Josh Hazlewood's return to the Australian XI for the Brisbane Test, highlighting Australia's bowling depth with Scott Boland as a reliable backup option.
title: Gilchrist unimpressed with Bumrah partners Siraj and Rana

description: Bank fixed deposit rates are expected to remain stable through FY25 due to sufficient liquidity from reduced credit expansion and a recent CRR cut.  While a downward trend is possible, actual rate reductions are contingent on the RBI lowering its repo rate.
title: RBI cuts CRR: Will bank fixed deposit rates come down soon?

description: Ousted Intel CEO Pat Gelsinger has called for prayers and fasting for the company's employees amid a turbulent period. Following a significant stock decline and workforce reductions, Gelsinger's departure was orchestrated by the board. Interim co-CEOs are in place as the search for a permanent replacement, potentially from outside Intel, begins.
title: Fired Intel CEO: Will fast this week for 100,000 Intel employees as they …

description: Mohammed Shami, the Indian fast bowler, unleashed a blistering unbeaten 32 off just 17 balls, smashing three fours and two sixes in a Syed Mushtaq Ali pre-quarter-final against Chandigarh. His late-innings blitz propelled Bengal from a struggling 114/8 to a respectable 159/9. Shami's aggressive knock came at a strike rate of 188.24, making him the second-highest scorer for Bengal.
title: Watch: Shami mayhem in SMAT, smokes 32 off just ...

description: The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) announced its second list of candidates for the Delhi Assembly elections. Deputy CM Manish Sisodia will contest from Jangpura, while educator Avdhash Ojha will run from Sisodia's current seat, Patparganj.  The AAP previously won 62 of 70 seats in the 2020 elections.
title: Delhi polls: AAP releases second list, fields Manish Sisodia from Jangpura

description: Actress Deepika Padukone made a surprise appearance at Diljit Dosanjh's Bengaluru concert, her first since giving birth.  She taught the Punjabi singer basic Kannada phrases.  A viral video of the interaction sparked humorous reactions online, with many joking that Diljit can now navigate Bengaluru's auto-rickshaws with ease.
title: Deepika Padukone turns Kannada teacher for Diljit Dosanjh: Netizens joke

description: Following India's significant loss to Australia in the second Border-Gavaskar Trophy Test, cricket icon Sunil Gavaskar lauded Virat Kohli's dedication. Despite a recent slump in form, Kohli was spotted practicing in the nets right after the match. Gavaskar praised Kohli's commitment and urged his teammates to emulate his work ethic.
title: 'Working hard ...': Gavaskar lauds Kohli despite poor outing

description: India's Test captain Rohit Sharma faced criticism for his subdued leadership and poor batting performance following a heavy defeat against Australia in the second Test at Adelaide. Experts, including Ravi Shastri and Sunil Gavaskar, urged Rohit to return to his opening position to regain his aggressive approach.
title: Rohit Sharma faces heat after Adelaide debacle

description: Opposition MPs, led by Rahul Gandhi, staged a protest and a satirical play targeting the government's handling of the Adani issue.  Impersonating PM Modi and Gautam Adani, they highlighted their alleged close relationship and influence.  While several opposition parties participated, TMC, SP, and NCP were notably absent, raising concerns about opposition unity.
title: Watch: Rahul takes a dig at PM Modi & Adani in a staged 'interview'

description: India is closely monitoring the evolving situation in Syria, where opposition forces have seized Damascus, prompting President Assad to seek refuge in Russia. The Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) urges all parties to uphold Syria's unity and sovereignty, advocating for a peaceful resolution.
title: 'Need for all parties to work towards preserving unity': MEA on Syria

description: Australian captain Pat Cummins led his team to victory in the second Test against India in Adelaide with a match-winning five-wicket haul (5/57). This was Cummins' eighth five-wicket haul as captain, tying him with Bishan Singh Bedi.  He also reached 50 wickets in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy and solidified his position as a leading wicket-taker in pink-ball Tests.
title: Pat Cummins equals Bishan Singh Bedi's record with Adelaide exploits

description: Mark Mobius believes the US Justice Department's indictment of Gautam Adani, was probably an overstepping of mandate. He anticipates a decrease in international corporate prosecutions under the Trump administration.
title: 'US DOJ has no business…’: Mobius’ strong words on Adani case

description: Prithvi Shaw's exclusion from the IPL auction sparked concern, prompting advice from former cricketer Basit Ali to prioritize his cricketing career and improve his game.  Ali urged Shaw to avoid the path of Vinod Kambli and focus on performance. Kevin Pietersen also earlier encouraged Shaw to focus on fitness and minimize social media presence for a successful comeback.
title: 'Prithvi Shaw saab, doosre Vinod Kambli mat bano'

description: Rahul Narwekar, BJP MLA, was re-elected unopposed as Maharashtra Assembly Speaker for a second term.  The Maha Vikas Aghadi did not contest.  His role is crucial in determining the Leader of Opposition, as the opposition holds less than 10% of the seats.  Narwekar previously served as Speaker from July 2022, notably handling Shiv Sena MLA disqualification petitions.
title: BJP's Rahul Narwekar re-elected Maharashtra assembly speaker unopposed

description: Pushpa 2: The Rule' saw a box office dip on its fifth day, earning ₹6.99 crore net in India. Despite the slowdown, the film's domestic net collection reached ₹536.44 crore, with a global total of ₹800 crore.  Strong North American performance and continued spot bookings suggest potential growth, aiming to surpass 'Kalki 2898 AD' as the year's highest-grossing Indian film.
title: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' box office collection Day 5

description: Rebel forces swiftly overthrew Bashar al-Assad's regime in Syria, prompting varied global reactions.  World leaders addressed the implications of Assad's fall, emphasizing peace, stability, and the need for a Syrian-led transition.  While some celebrated the end of Assad's rule, others expressed caution and called for political dialogue.
title: 'Fundamental act of justice': World leaders react to fall of Assad regime in Syria

description: Former Australian cricket captains Michael Clarke and Mark Taylor criticised Indian bowler Mohammed Siraj's appealing style during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Clarke suggested Siraj should be fined for appealing LBWs without acknowledging the umpire, while Taylor called on senior Indian players to address Siraj's conduct, deeming it disrespectful to the game and umpires.
title: Clarke wants Siraj penalised and it's not for Head send-off!
Nagpur hotel receives bomb threat email

description: Tensions flared in Hyderabad as BRS legislators, sporting "Adani-Revanth Bhai Bhai" t-shirts, were barred from entering the Assembly. BRS leader KTR accused Congress of hypocrisy, citing Rahul Gandhi's Adani criticisms while alleging a close relationship between Revanth Reddy and Adani.
title: BRS legislators wear T-shirts reading 'Adani-Revanth Bhai Bhai', stopped by police

description: Syrian rebels liberated Saydnaya Prison, a notorious detention center near Damascus, revealing horrific conditions and atrocities committed under Assad's regime.  Thousands of prisoners, including children, endured torture, starvation, and neglect.  Emotional reunions followed as families embraced freed loved ones after years of separation. The liberation symbolized the end of Assad's oppressive rule.
title: Inside Syria's 'human slaughterhouse': Rebels detail atrocities of Saydnaya prison

description: Juan Soto secured a record-breaking 15-year, $765 million contract with the New York Mets, making him the highest-paid player in baseball history. The deal surpasses Shohei Ohtani's previous record and includes a $75 million signing bonus.
title: Juan Soto signs 15-year, $765M megadeal with New York Mets

description: The IRCTC website and app experienced an outage, causing difficulties for Indian Railways passengers booking tickets.  Users reported login issues, problems searching schedules and fares, and trouble completing transactions.  The outage, starting around 10 AM, impacted both the website and app, with users taking to X (formerly Twitter) to express their frustrations.
title: IRCTC down: Users not able to books tickets on app and website

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol faced a travel ban following his declaration of martial law, which sparked impeachment attempts and the detention of his former defense minister.  Though he survived impeachment, investigations continue into alleged rebellion, with top military commanders also removed.  Yoon expressed regret for the martial law decision amid ongoing political turmoil and opposition challenges.
title: South Korea orders travel ban for President Yoon

description: Joe Root's remarkable form continues as he notched his 36th Test century against New Zealand. Since 2021, he has amassed an astounding 19 Test hundreds, leaving rivals like Kohli, Smith, and Williamson trailing. Root is closing in on Ricky Ponting's second-place spot on the all-time Test run-scorers list, with even Sachin Tendulkar's seemingly untouchable record within his sights.
title: Unstoppable Joe! Has Root mania put Sachin's records under threat?

description: The NYPD released new images of the suspect in the Wednesday shooting death of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. One shows him in a taxi after the incident. The suspect, wearing a mask and dark clothing, took a cab from the Upper West Side to a bus station near the George Washington Bridge.
title: NYPD releases new photos of suspected killer of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson

description: Jeff Bezos, Amazon's founder, champions a unique meeting style.  He prepares with detailed memos but encourages unstructured discussions for sparking innovation. While valuing these "messy" meetings, he acknowledges the need for structured ones.  Bezos also stresses candid conversations and optimistic leadership for building strong teams and navigating challenges.
title: Amazon founder Jeff Bezos says he is rarely on time in meetings

description: President Biden and the family of Austin Tice, an American journalist missing in Syria since 2012, expressed renewed hope for his return. While lacking definitive proof of his location, Biden believes Tice is alive. The US government, through various channels, has been working to secure his release, though the Syrian government previously denied holding him.
title: Biden, Austin Tice's family hopes alive after journalist disappears in Syria

description: Former US President Donald Trump met with various world leaders in Paris, including Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, whom he called a "real live wire." He discussed NATO finances with French President Emmanuel Macron and had a cordial exchange with First Lady Jill Biden.
title: 'I was with her a lot': Trump describes Meloni as 'real live wire' after Paris dinner

description: India's Test batting woes continue, with repeated collapses leading to four losses in recent matches. Former opener Aakash Chopra highlighted the struggles, particularly in first innings, emphasizing the need to acknowledge the problem. Captain Rohit Sharma echoed the concerns after the Adelaide defeat, admitting the team's batting fell short.
title: 'Improvement starts, when you first accept problem hai'

description: Congress leader Manickam Tagore on Monday gave an adjournment motion notice in Lok Sabha and expressed concern over the clean chits given to Maharashtra Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar and Andhra Pradesh CM Chandrababu Naidu in high-profile cases.
title: Manickam Tagore expresses concern over clean chits to Ajit Pawar, Naidu

description: At least three people were killed in suspected country-made bomb explosions in West Bengal's Murshidabad district on Monday morning. Police have launched an investigation to determine the exact circumstances of the incident.
title: 3 dead in bomb blasts in West Bengal's Murshidabad

description: Over 40 Delhi schools received bomb threats demanding $30,000, causing widespread panic and student evacuations. The chilling emails warned of hidden explosives and potential injuries. Chief Minister Atishi criticized the central government's security failures, while Arvind Kejriwal demanded answers from Home Minister Amit Shah.
title: 'You all deserve to suffer, lose limbs': Over 40 Delhi schools receive bomb threat

description: US forces launched airstrikes against over 75 ISIS targets in Syria, utilizing B-52s, F-15s, and A-10s.  President Biden declared the collapse of the Assad regime a "fundamental act of justice," highlighting the opportunity for Syrians to rebuild after decades of conflict.  Rebels seized control of Homs, celebrating the end of Assad's rule as he reportedly fled to Russia.
title: US targets over 75 Isis sites in Syria

description: Indian Foreign Secretary Vikram Misri's upcoming visit to Bangladesh aims to mend strained relations following a recent political upheaval.  Bangladesh seeks improved ties based on "fairness" while also pursuing the extradition of former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, currently sheltered in India.  Key bilateral issues, including border management and trade, will be on the agenda.
title: 'Expect our relations with India to be based on fairness': Bangladesh

description: President-elect Trump and Prince William met in Paris, discussing various topics, including William's family. Trump praised William's appearance and demeanor.  The conversation also touched upon the health challenges faced by King Charles III and Kate Middleton, who recently completed chemotherapy for cancer.
title: 'He’s a good looking guy': What Trump said after meeting Prince William in Paris

description: Rebel leader Ahmed al-Sharaa, formerly known as Abu Mohammed al-Jolani, declared a "historic" victory from Damascus's Umayyad Mosque after his Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS) group seized control of the Syrian capital, forcing President Bashar al-Assad to flee to Moscow. Al-Sharaa celebrated the end of Assad's oppressive rule and the purification of Syria from Iranian influence and sectarianism.
title: 'Syria being purified': Watch rebel leader Jolani's victory speech from mosque

description: Over 40 private schools in Delhi, including DPS Vasant Kunj, DPS R.K. Puram, and G.D. Goenka, received bomb threats via email demanding $30,000.  Authorities, including bomb squads and dog squads, investigated but found nothing suspicious. Students were sent home as a precaution. This follows a court order for a bomb threat SOP.
title: Bomb threat to over 40 Delhi schools trigger panic and security scramble

description: Rajasthan braces for a cold wave from November 9th to 14th, with temperatures expected to plummet by 4°C in western and northern regions.  Mount Abu shivered at 4.4°C, while Jaipur, after its coldest morning at 9.4°C, saw a slight reprieve. Northerly winds persist, promising chilly days ahead.
title: Cold wave conditions to intensify in west & north Rajasthan from Dec 9

description: Josh Allen's record-breaking performance against the Rams, including six touchdowns (three passing, three rushing), propelled him into MVP contention despite the Bills' narrow loss.  His 424 total yards and 51.88 fantasy points highlighted his dual-threat dominance, though Buffalo now trails Kansas City in the AFC race.  While the loss stings, Allen's exceptional play solidifies his status as a rising superstar.
title: Josh Allen makes NFL history with 6 TDs against Rams

description: Delhi police investigated two Delhi schools after bomb threats.  DPS RK Puram and GD Goenka Paschim Vihar received email threats.  Students were sent home.  Police, fire services, and bomb squads searched the schools.  The threats follow a recent court order for a bomb threat action plan.
title: 2 Delhi schools receive bomb threat emails, children sent back home

description: India's crushing 10-wicket defeat against Australia in the second Test has sparked calls for Mohammed Shami's inclusion in the bowling attack. Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali has urged India to send Shami for the third Test in Brisbane. However, Captain Rohit Sharma revealed Shami experienced knee swelling after domestic matches, delaying his return.
title: 'Agar Shami ko 4th Test ke liye bula rahe, toh na hi bulayen'

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2: The Rule" shattered box office records, grossing over Rs 800 crore worldwide in its extended opening weekend. The film achieved the highest opening day and weekend collections for an Indian film, both domestically and internationally. Its Hindi version dominated with Rs 285.7 crore, contributing significantly to the film's estimated Rs 529.45 crore India net in just four days.
title: Pushpa 2 box office collection crosses Rs 800 crore worldwide

description: Jay-Z and Sean "Diddy" Combs are facing a civil lawsuit alleging the rape of a 13-year-old girl in 2000. The lawsuit, filed by Tony Buzbee, claims the assault occurred at a post-MTV Video Music Awards party. The accuser alleges she was given a drink, felt 'woozy' prompting her to lie down in room where she was then assaulted by Carter while Combs and another woman watched.
title: Jay-Z accused of raping 13-yr-old with Diddy in bombshell civil lawsuit

description: Vintage car enthusiasts in Lucknow, India, showcased over 15 classic vehicles, including a 1928 Ford and a 1945 Jaguar, in a 20-kilometer drive.  Owners and mechanics discussed the challenges and passion involved in preserving these historical machines.  Uttar Pradesh Tourism supported the event, aiming to promote the city's rich heritage and boost tourism.
title: From Baby Austins to WWII Jeeps: Lucknow hosts spectacular vintage car parade

description: Delhi Capitals' new coach Hemang Badani revealed that Rishabh Pant's departure stemmed from the player's desire to test his market value, contradicting co-owner Parth Jindal's prior statement. Pant secured a record-breaking ₹27 crore deal with Lucknow Super Giants, despite Delhi's attempts to retain him.
title: 'Rishabh Pant wanted to test the market for more money'

description: A heated exchange between Indian bowler Mohammed Siraj and Australian batsman Travis Head during the second Test in Adelaide has drawn ICC scrutiny. Siraj's fiery send-off after dismissing Head sparked a war of words and crowd disapproval. Conflicting accounts emerged, with Head claiming he complimented Siraj before the dismissal, while Siraj accused Head of abusing him.
title: Siraj, Travis Head may face ICC disciplinary action

description: The CFPB announced it would supervise Google's payment arm, citing potential violations related to consumer complaints and erroneous transfers. Google immediately challenged the decision in court, arguing the product in question is discontinued and poses no risk to consumers.  This move comes amid increased scrutiny of tech companies' financial services by the Biden administration.
title: Google is suing this US govt agency; says as a matter of common sense ...

description: Microsoft President Brad Smith cautioned against underestimating China's technological advancements at the Web Summit. He highlighted China's progress in numerous tech areas, emphasizing the future competition between American and Chinese companies. Smith also urged US-European collaboration to drive global economic growth and technological advancements, while acknowledging the complexities of American companies operating in China.
title: Microsoft president: I think one danger is that people who don’t go to China ...

description: A witchdoctor in Ahmedabad, Navalsinh Chavda, died in police custody after allegedly confessing to killing 12 people, including family members.  He poisoned them to avoid medical expenses and end domestic disputes. Chavda's death is also under investigation, raising suspicions. He was apprehended while attempting another ritualistic murder.
title: 'Poison with sodium nitrite': ‘Witch doctor’ who killed 12 dies in police custody

description: Three BNP-affiliated organizations in Dhaka protested against an attack on Bangladesh's diplomatic mission in India and alleged attempts to incite communal unrest.  They submitted a memorandum to the Indian High Commission, with a senior BNP member warning of resistance against perceived Indian aggression.  Concurrently, Bangladesh's home ministry ordered undocumented foreign nationals to legalize their status.
title: BNP-linked groups rally to protest attack on Agartala mission

description: India's gross foreign direct investment (FDI) surged by nearly 29% to $42.3 billion in the first half of the current fiscal year, reaching a cumulative $1 trillion since April 2000. This growth, following two years of decline, signals renewed investor confidence. Equity inflows saw a notable 45% increase.
title: FDI inflows up 29% at $42 billion in April-September after 2-year fall

description: A Broadway show about Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's relationship is reportedly in the works, slated for a 2025 debut.  The 75-minute production, budgeted at $7.5 million, awaits the couple's approval.  Writers are drawn to Kelce's 'guy next door' persona, aiming to portray their love story on stage following Swift's Eras Tour conclusion.
title: Taylor Swift & Travis Kelce could be Broadway’s next big drama

description: Kerala police face a dilemma with 35 FIRs related to the Hema Committee report on sexual abuse in the Malayalam film industry.  Survivors are hesitant to pursue legal action, and the passage of time has hampered investigations.  Actor Mala Parvathy has challenged the probe in the Supreme Court, while a nodal officer has been appointed to support survivors facing threats.
title: Survivors' reluctance stalls 35 SIT cases based on Hema panel report

description: India is constructing a 1,643-km fence along its border with Myanmar to address security concerns, smuggling, and human trafficking. The $3.1 billion project, slated for completion within 10 years, includes provisions for controlled cross-border movement through biometric-enabled gates.  While some local communities oppose the fence, authorities emphasize its necessity for national security and regulated trade.
title: Myanmar border fencing gathers pace, BRO to complete project in 10 yrs

description: Karnataka witnessed a 26% surge in women income tax return filers over the past five years, reaching 14.3 lakh in 2023-24.  This growth outpaces the overall filer increase, with women now comprising a third of all filers. Nationally, Maharashtra leads with 36.8 lakh women filers, followed by Gujarat and Uttar Pradesh.
title: At 36.8 lakh, Maharashtra tops list of women ITR filers; Gujarat 2nd

description: Bangladesh's foreign affairs adviser acknowledges a recent "stalemate" with India following reported attacks on Hindus.  He expresses optimism for improved relations through upcoming foreign secretary-level talks, focusing on trade, border management, and other key bilateral issues.  Indian Foreign Secretary Vikram Misri's visit marks the first high-level interaction since Bangladesh's interim government took power.
title: Bangladesh 'optimistic' of ending stalemate in relations with India
